modules.description: The library provides GADT-based combinators for constructing runtime type representations of OCaml values, supporting atomic types (booleans, integers, strings) and compound structures like records, variants, lists, and recursive types. It enables generic operations such as serialization, equality checks, and JSON encoding/decoding for structured data, with optimized handling of nested or mutually recursive types. This facilitates tasks like binary data parsing, schema-driven data manipulation, and type-safe generic programming without intermediate format conversions.
